# ROSE CARE GUIDE 🌹  
(High-maintenance flowering ornamental — Precision plant)

---

## 🌹 Plant Nature & Behaviour Model

Roses are biologically dramatic, metabolically demanding, and ruthlessly honest.

Core traits:

✔ Extremely heavy feeder  
✔ Flowers on NEW GROWTH  
✔ Requires aggressive pruning  
✔ Highly pest & disease prone  
✔ Sensitive to nutrient imbalance  
✔ Loves sunlight (NON-NEGOTIABLE)  
✔ Continuous bloom potential

Critical mental model:

Rose = Engineered flowering machine.

Everything revolves around:

✔ Nutrition  
✔ Pruning  
✔ Sunlight  
✔ Airflow

---

## ☀️ LIGHT REQUIREMENT (ABSOLUTE RULE)

Roses LOVE sun.

✔ Minimum 6–8 hrs direct sunlight  
✔ Full sun ideal

Low light symptoms:

✔ Leggy growth  
✔ Few flowers  
✔ Small blooms  
✔ Weak stems  
✔ Disease explosion

Sunlight = Flower fuel.

---

## 🌱 SOIL MANAGEMENT (CRITICAL)

Ideal soil behaviour:

✔ Excellent drainage  
✔ Loose & aerated  
✔ Rich organic matter  
✔ Never compacted

Rose roots HATE:

✘ Wet suffocating soil  
✘ Hard compacted soil

---

### ✅ ORGANIC FOUNDATION

Every 30–45 days:

✔ Vermicompost → 300–500 g  
✔ Cow Manure → Light handful

Why:

✔ Sustained nutrient base  
✔ Soil structure improvement  
✔ Better bloom quality

Optional booster:

✔ Humic Acid Drench

Dose:
2–3 g/L

Frequency:
Every 30–45 days

Why:

✔ Root stimulation  
✔ Better nutrient uptake  
✔ Reduces fertilizer stress

---

## 💧 WATERING STRATEGY

Golden rule:

✔ Deep watering  
✔ Allow partial drying  
✔ Avoid constant wet soil

Typical rhythm:

✔ Every 2–4 days (heat dependent)

Classic rose killers:

✘ Overwatering → Root rot → Black leaves  
✘ Underwatering → Bud drop

Stability > Frequency.

---

## 🧪 FERTILIZER PROGRAM (ROSES = HEAVY FEEDERS)

Roses consume nutrients aggressively.

---

### 🌿 GENERAL GROWTH PHASE

✔ NPK 19:19:19

Dose:
1 g/L

Frequency:
Every 7–10 days

Why:

✔ Sustains rapid metabolism  
✔ Leaf & shoot development  
✔ Bud formation support

---

### 🌹 FLOWERING PHASE (MOST IMPORTANT)

✔ SOP 00:00:50 (Potassium Engine)

Dose:
1 g/L

Frequency:
Every 10–14 days

Why:

✔ Bud formation  
✔ Flower size  
✔ Colour intensity  
✔ Bloom longevity  
✔ Stem strength

MOST COMMON ROSE FAILURE:

❌ Potassium deficiency

---

### 🦴 CALCIUM SUPPORT (VERY IMPORTANT)

✔ Calcium Nitrate

Dose:
1 g/L

Frequency:
Every 20–30 days

Why:

✔ Strong stems  
✔ Bud durability  
✔ Prevents bud drop

Do NOT mix with SOP.

Alternate cycles.

---

### 🌿 MAGNESIUM BOOST (EXTREMELY IMPORTANT)

✔ Epsom Salt

Dose:
1 g/L

Frequency:
Every 20–30 days

Why:

✔ Deep green foliage  
✔ Improves photosynthesis  
✔ Increases bud production

Magnesium deficiency = VERY common in roses.

---

### 🔬 MICRONUTRIENTS (CRITICAL)

✔ Micronutrient Mix

Frequency:
Every 30–45 days

Why:

✔ Prevents chlorosis  
✔ Sustains flowering rhythm  
✔ Improves bloom quality

Deficiency symptoms:

✔ Yellow leaves with green veins  
✔ Small flowers  
✔ Weak stems

---

### 🌊 SEAWEED EXTRACT (EXCELLENT FOR ROSES)

Dose:
2–3 ml/L

Frequency:
Every 20–30 days

Why:

✔ Flower stimulation  
✔ Stress buffering  
✔ Root vigor  
✔ Bud retention

---

## 🐛 PEST MANAGEMENT (ROSES = PEST MAGNET)

Common pests:

• Aphids  
• Thrips (VERY COMMON)  
• Spider mites (MAJOR ENEMY)  
• Mealybugs  
• Caterpillars  

Roses attract EVERYTHING.

---

## 🚨 SPIDER MITES (MOST DANGEROUS)

Symptoms:

✔ Tiny yellow speckles  
✔ Fine webs  
✔ Leaf dullness  
✔ Rapid leaf drop

Cause:

✔ Heat + dry air

---

### ✅ PREVENTIVE BASELINE (NON-NEGOTIABLE)

✔ Neem Oil

Dose:
3–5 ml/L + Wetting agent

Frequency:
Every 7–10 days

YES — Roses require aggressive prevention.

---

### ✅ SAP SUCKING PESTS

✔ Thiamethoxam (if infestation visible)

Use only when needed.

---

### ✅ THRIPS / FLOWER DAMAGE

✔ Indoxacarb / Chlorantraniliprole (rotate)

---

## 🍄 DISEASE MANAGEMENT (MOST CRITICAL PART OF ROSE CARE)

Common diseases:

✔ Black spot (MOST COMMON)  
✔ Powdery mildew  
✔ Rust  
✔ Leaf spot  

Roses are disease magnets.

---

### ✅ PREVENTIVE FUNGICIDE (CRITICAL)

✔ Hexaconazole 5% SC

Frequency:
Every 15–30 days

Why:

✔ Prevents fungal outbreaks  
✔ Essential in humid climates  
✔ Stops black spot cycles

MOST COMMON ROSE FAILURE:

❌ No preventive fungicide

---

### ✅ STRONG PROTECTION / CURATIVE

✔ Azoxystrobin + Mancozeb (Powder)

Use when:

✔ Visible spotting  
✔ Rainy season  
✔ Persistent leaf damage

---

## ✂️ PRUNING STRATEGY (THIS DEFINES ROSE PERFORMANCE)

Rose = Pruning-dependent species.

No pruning → Ugly plant → Few flowers.

---

### ✅ WHEN TO PRUNE

✔ Major pruning → Seasonal  
✔ Light pruning → Continuous  
✔ After flowering flush

---

### ✅ PRUNING OBJECTIVES

✔ Stimulate new shoots  
✔ Increase flowering points  
✔ Control structure  
✔ Remove diseased wood  
✔ Improve airflow

---

### ✅ WHAT TO REMOVE

✔ Dead branches  
✔ Weak thin stems  
✔ Crossing branches  
✔ Inward growth  
✔ Diseased wood  
✔ Old woody unproductive stems

Goal:

✔ Open vase structure  
✔ Airflow dominance  
✔ Sunlight penetration

---

### ✅ PRUNING INTENSITY

✔ Roses tolerate HARD pruning  
✔ Aggressive cutback beneficial  
✔ Encourages explosive new growth

---

### ✅ CUTTING TECHNIQUE (CRITICAL)

✔ Cut above outward-facing bud  
✔ Slight angled cut  
✔ Clean sharp pruner  
✔ No stubs

Wrong cuts → Dieback + Disease entry.

---

## 🌹 COMMON ROSE PROBLEMS DECODED

Lots of leaves, few flowers → Excess nitrogen / Low potassium  
Small flowers → Potassium deficiency  
Bud drop → Stress / Calcium imbalance / Thrips  
Yellow leaves → Magnesium / micronutrient deficiency  
Black spots → Fungal disease  
Leaves curling → Aphids / Thrips / Stress  
Wilted new shoots → Spider mites / Root stress  
Dirty ugly buds → Thrips (VERY COMMON)

---

## ⚠️ HIGH-IMPACT FAILURE POINTS

Roses struggle mostly from:

1) Insufficient sunlight  
2) No pruning (EXTREMELY COMMON)  
3) Potassium deficiency  
4) Magnesium deficiency  
5) No fungicide prevention  
6) Poor airflow  
7) Overwatering  
8) Thrips & spider mites

---

## 🎯 OPTIMAL CARE PHILOSOPHY

Roses thrive on:

✔ Full sun dominance  
✔ Frequent feeding cycles  
✔ Potassium-rich flowering support  
✔ Aggressive pruning strategy  
✔ Preventive fungicide discipline  
✔ Regular magnesium supplementation  
✔ Strong airflow  
✔ Neem-based pest prevention  
✔ Rapid intervention when issues appear

Roses are brutally fair plants.

Precision in → Beauty out.

Neglect in → Chaos out.

